// Man page for ps
manPs="PS(1)                            X Shell Manual                            PS(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    ps - used to view current running process
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>ps</b> [<b>-u</b> USER] [<b>-c</b> CMD]
    <b>ps</b> <b>-m</b>
    <b>ps</b> <b>-l</b> [PAUSE]
    <b>ps</b> <b>-w</b> [PAUSE]
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Display active processes. Modes for viewing, managing, locking new
    processes, and real-time monitoring. <b>-m</b>, <b>-w</b>, and <b>-l</b>
    are mutually exclusive. For filesystem lockdown see <b>ids</b>.
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>ps</b>
    View active processes
    List all running processes

    <b>-m</b>
    Manage processes
    Interactive kill-by-PID mode

    <b>-l</b> [PAUSE]
    Lock process list
    Kill any process not present at start. Press <b>q</b> to stop.
    PAUSE is poll interval in seconds (default 1).

    <b>-u</b> USER
    Filter processes by username

    <b>-c</b> CMD
    Filter processes by command name

    <b>-w</b> [PAUSE]
    Watch mode
    Alert on process launch and exit. Press <b>q</b> to stop.
    PAUSE is poll interval in seconds (default 1).

<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Basic View</color>
    <b>ps</b>
    List processes

    <color=#e4ff34># Management</color>
    <b>ps -m</b>
    Manage processes

    <color=#e4ff34># Lock Mode</color>
    <b>ps -l</b>
    Kill newly launched processes

    <b>ps -l 5</b>
    Same, poll every 5 seconds

    <color=#e4ff34># Watch Mode</color>
    <b>ps -w</b>
    Real-time launch/exit alerts

    <b>ps -w 5</b>
    Same, poll every 5 seconds
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>lsof</b>, <b>kill</b>, <b>ids</b>"
